!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

consumption /kənˈsʌmpʃən/

1. N-UNCOUNT The consumption of fuel or natural resources is the act of using them or the amount used. 消耗 

例： The laws have led to a reduction in fuel consumption in the U.S. 这些法律已导致美国燃料消耗的降低。 

2. N-UNCOUNT The consumption of food or drink is the act of eating or drinking something, or the amount eaten or drunk. 食用; 饮用 [正式] 

例： Most of the wine was unfit for human consumption. 大多数酒都是不适合人类饮用的。 

3. N-UNCOUNT Consumption is the act of buying and using things. 消费 

例： They were prepared to put people out of work and reduce consumption by strangling the whole economy. 他们准备让人们失业、降低消费，由此来遏制整个经济。

</div>

